{%- comment -%}
  Recently viewed (spec §5.2): session-persistent, PDP + cart page only,
  auto-hides under 2 items. Architecture trade-off worth calling out: unlike
  wishlist/compare (which only ever need to re-render products already on the
  current page, so storing just an id is enough), recently-viewed has to show
  products from OTHER pages the visitor already navigated away from — there's
  no Liquid object for those on this page load. Rather than adding a second
  network round trip (fetch each stored handle's /products/{handle}.js on
  every PDP visit), this stores one small display snapshot (title, url,
  image, price) per product directly in localStorage at view-time, then
  assets/recently-viewed.js renders straight from that — zero extra requests,
  at the cost of a stale price/title if a merchant changes either later. A
  reasonable trade for a below-the-fold, non-transactional module.

  Accepts: product (required).
{%- endcomment -%}
<div class="recently-viewed" data-recently-viewed hidden>
  <script type="application/json" data-recently-viewed-current>
    {
      "handle": {{ product.handle | json }},
      "title": {{ product.title | json }},
      "url": {{ product.url | json }},
      "image": {{ product.featured_image | image_url: width: 400 | json }},
      "price": {{ product.price | json }},
      "compareAtPrice": {{ product.compare_at_price | json }},
      "available": {{ product.available | json }},
      "i18n": {
        "salePrice": {{ 'products.product.price.sale_price' | t | json }},
        "regularPrice": {{ 'products.product.price.regular_price' | t | json }}
      }
    }
  </script>
  <h2 class="recently-viewed__title text-h4">{{ 'products.product.recently_viewed_heading' | t }}</h2>
  <div class="grid grid-cols-4" data-recently-viewed-grid></div>
</div>
